<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>A tactical role-playing game (abbreviated as TRPG; sometimes referred to as strategy role-playing game, or SRPG) is a type of video game which incorporates elements of traditional role-playing video games and strategy games. In Japan these games are known as "Simulation RPGs"
                  <br><br>This sub-genre of role-playing game principally refers to games which incorporate elements from strategy games as an alternative to traditional role-playing game (RPG) systems. Like standard RPGs, the player controls a finite party and battles a similar number of enemies. And like other RPGs, death is usually temporary. But this genre incorporates strategic gameplay such as tactical movement on an isometric grid.
                  <br><br>Gunho Brigade is a tactical RPG published by Tomy Corporation in the year 2000 for the Playstation One console that takes place in a futuristic world where a group of people try to combat the evil robot forces that controls the World. The game begins when the 2 main characters of the game are being pursued by a group of machines in a desert canyon.
                  <br><br>The gameplay is the usual in this kind of games, the player units got a limited range of movement and different attack, the big difference with other Tactical RPG games is that after selecting the movements that game graphics changes to a 3d view in which the attacks are displayed.
                  <br><br>To advance through the story (that is displayed using anime video sequences the player have to pass the missions.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Directing the opening and ending of each story chapter by anime voice , human drama and narrative story structure @ 26.
                  <br><br>When you direct the action automatic animation generation system ? A, generate a battle scene in real time, the pattern is infinite.
                  <br><br>B character design is great masters of painting ? ??compelling characters anime Akihiro Ito, Akihiro Ito, by the teacher.
                  <br><br>Seki Tomokazu C, such as Kikuko Inoue, appoint a gorgeous actors!
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>SCIFI, Futuristic & Anime themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

